                                    <h3>The medical exam and evaluation is just a formality</h3>
                                    <p style="display: none;">Your health history is instrumental in setting your premium. Occupation, hobbies, medical history, family history, and driving record give an insurer a window into your health and even likelihood to put your life at risk. All of these are factors in setting your premium. For healthy people like you, you could see premiums that are less than half of those paid by the average insured.</p>
