                                    <img src="resources/images/percentage.svg">
                                    <h3>My Premiums Are Tax Deductible</h3>
                                    <p style="display: none;">In most cases, premiums are not tax deductible. But the good news is, since your premiums come from after tax dollars, the entire value of your life insurance is paid to your beneficiaries, non-taxable. Contact your tax advisor regarding questions about possible income, estate and gift tax consequences.</p>
                                    <a href="#" class="secondary">Read More</a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-6 clearfix icon-misconception">
                                    <img src="resources/images/ribbon.svg">
                                    <h3>Only The Breadwinner Needs Life Insurance</h3>
                                    <p style="display: none;">Most people think that since a non-working partner makes no income, there is nothing there to insure. The loss of a non-working partner would require a need for additional services to care for your family, such as childcare. In addition, life insurance allows the surviving partner to take some unpaid time off work to help the family adjust to their loss.</p>
